{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.10"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.10","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Update your code to make use of the new state sharing tools in the library, such as the "},{"code":"Shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"property wrapper, and the "},{"code":"appStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"fileStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" persistence strategies."}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.19","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.18","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.16","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.15","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.14","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.13","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.12","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.11","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.9","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.8","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.7","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.6","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.5","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.4"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. This version of the library only introduced new"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"APIs and did not deprecate any existing APIs."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Before following this migration guide be sure you have fully migrated to the newest","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tools of version 1.9. See ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" for more information.","type":"text"}]}],"style":"important","type":"aside"},{"text":"Sharing state","level":2,"anchor":"Sharing-state","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The new tools added are concerned with allowing one to seamlessly share state with many parts of an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"application that is easy to understand, and most importantly, testable. See the dedicated","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState"},{"text":" article for more information on how to use these new tools.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To share state in one feature with another feature, simply use the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" property wrapper:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared var signUpData: SignUpData","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This will require that "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SignUpData"},{"type":"text","text":" be passed in from the parent, and any changes made to this state"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will be instantly observed by all features holding onto it."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Further, there are persistence strategies one can employ in ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". For example, if you want any","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"changes of ","type":"text"},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to be automatically persisted to the file system you can use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"fileStorage(_:decoder:encoder:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and specify a URL:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared(.fileStorage(URL(\/* ... *\/) var signUpData = SignUpData()","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Upon app launch the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signUpData"},{"type":"text","text":" will be populated from disk, and any changes made to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signUpData"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will automatically be persisted to disk. Further, if the disk version changes, all instances of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signUpData"},{"type":"text","text":" in the application will automatically update."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is another persistence strategy for storing simple data types in user defaults, called"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"appStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". It can refer to a value in user defaults by a string"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"key:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@ObservableState ","struct State {","  @Shared(.appStorage(\"isOn\")) var isOn = false","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Similar to ","type":"text"},{"code":"fileStorage(_:decoder:encoder:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", upon launch of the application the initial","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"value of ","type":"text"},{"code":"isOn","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be populated from user defaults, and any change to ","type":"text"},{"code":"isOn","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be automatically","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"persisted to user defaults. Further, if the user defaults value changes, all instances of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isOn"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the application will automatically update."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That is the basics of sharing data. Be sure to see the dedicated "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" article"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for more detailed information."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"role":"article","title":"Migrating to 1.10","roleHeading":"Article"},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture/Reducer()":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Helps implement the conformance to the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","iden